## Data Layer

### Database (Room, WAL mode)
| Table | Purpose |
|---|---|
| Session | One row per started workout (dayKey, startedAt, finishedAt) |
| LoggedExercise | One row per exercise in a session (effortRating, note, skipped) |
| LoggedSet | One row per set (weight, reps, isPr) |
| DayNameOverride | User-renamed day labels |
| ExerciseCustomization | Persistent exercise swaps (name + unit override) |
| UnlockedTrophy | Trophy IDs + unlock timestamp |
| CardioEntry | Cardio logs (type, duration, distance, effort, restReason, note) |
| MoodEntry | Post-workout mood per session |

### Repositories
- WorkoutRepository — session + set + exercise CRUD, mood recording, active session observe
- CustomizationRepository — day name overrides, exercise customizations
- TrophyRepository — unlock evaluation + persistence, stats snapshot fan-out
- CardioRepository — cardio CRUD, weekly minutes flow
- StatsRepository — all stats queries for the Stats tab

### Preferences (DataStore)
- `welcomed` flag
- `lastDeloadAtSessionCount` for deload tracking

### Domain Utilities
- PrDetector — compares new set against historical max
- VolumeCalculator — weight × reps per set → total lb
- WeightParser — parses weight text to Double lb ("45", "2 plates", "BW", "45lb")
- TrophyEvaluator — pure function, stats snapshot → set of unlocked trophy IDs
- RestTimerController — coroutine-based countdown state machine (start / pause / resume / reset / stop)

### DI
- Hilt throughout (ViewModels, Repositories, DAOs, Clock)
- Clock abstraction (SystemClock + fakeable for tests)

