### Build order recommendation

**DONE → Tier 1** (chart bugs, heatmap labels, cardio mini-chart)
**DONE → Tier 2** (forgiving input, long-press copy, use-last chip, weight suggestion, auto-progression, quick start)
**Next → Tier 3** (rest timer notification + quick-extend, smart defaults, haptics, PR animation, edit sets, undo, session warning, foreground notification, skip remaining, in-session progress, next-up preview, predicted end time, per-exercise status chip)
**Then → Tier 4** (streak, PR hall-of-fame, exercise history graph, goal weights, session comparison, monthly calendar, trophy nudge, new trophies batch, session tags, on-this-day memory)
**Then → Tier 5** (settings screen, unit toggle, empty states, per-exercise timer, notes search, session type markers, reset options, locale settings, intensity pre-selector)
**Then → Tier 6** (analytics — needs weeks of real data to be meaningful; start with density score + honesty index since those work with small datasets)
**Later → Tier 7** (custom programming, AMRAP/advanced set types, widget, sample data mode)
**Eventually → Tier 9** (Polish — after Tier 5 is solid and Tier 3 haptics are tuned)
**Someday → Tier 8** (future scope / AI-adjacent / intelligence features that need months of data)

